## 💳 **BANK TRANSACTION AUTO-IMPORT - REALISTIC OPTIONS**

### **🎯 OPTION 1: Excel Power Query + Bank CSV (EASIEST TO IMPLEMENT)**

**How It Works:**
- Client downloads monthly CSV from their bank (most banks offer this)
- Excel Power Query automatically imports and categorizes the CSV
- One-click refresh updates all transactions

**Client Setup Required:**
1. Save bank CSV to specific folder (like `C:\TaxTracker\BankImports\`)
2. Click "Refresh Data" in Excel once per month
3. Review and confirm auto-categorizations

**Your Implementation:**
- Set up Power Query connection in Excel template
- Create smart categorization rules (vendor name matching)
- Pre-program common business expense categories
- Include video tutorial showing bank CSV download process

**Pros:**
- ✅ Works with 95% of banks
- ✅ Built into Excel (no additional software)
- ✅ Client keeps control of their login credentials
- ✅ One-time setup, minimal monthly effort

**Cons:**
- ❌ Still requires monthly CSV download from bank
- ❌ 5-10 minutes monthly client effort

---

### **🎯 OPTION 2: Receipt Apps Integration (MEDIUM COMPLEXITY)**

**How It Works:**
- Client uses existing apps like Expensify, Receipt Bank, or Shoeboxed
